        <p class="speculative-lead">I start from a feeling &mdash; a grokking of how life might be when technology matures. I go on to live as if it&rsquo;s already here.</p>
        <p>I build working prototypes of future interfaces, not concept renders. Childhood science fiction never left; it just changed medium. The method: imagine it, build it, live with it, observe where it fails and where it excels.</p>

        <div class="speculative-methods">
          <div class="speculative-method">
            <strong>Prototype the future</strong>
            <span>Working implementations over concept renders. If you can&rsquo;t use it daily, it&rsquo;s not real yet.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="speculative-method">
            <strong>Live with it</strong>
            <span>Use the system every day. Observe friction. The interesting question isn&rsquo;t &ldquo;what can this AI do?&rdquo; but &ldquo;what kind of environment emerges from long-term human-AI interaction?&rdquo;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="speculative-method">
            <strong>Digital body, not second brain</strong>
            <span>Memory + tools + action capability + sensory systems. Growing a symbiotic ecosystem.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="speculative-method">
            <strong>Compassionate co-learning</strong>
            <span>Training in acceptance and commitment therapy, years of coaching, and mindfulness practice shape how I approach the agentic future &mdash; not with control, but with psychological flexibility. Notice what works, accept uncertainty, stay values-driven. The same skills that help people live fuller lives help us learn to coexist with autonomous systems.</span>
